\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}]}],\"bg_type\":\"color\",\"bg_color\":\"hsl(182, 55%, 58%)\"},{\"_type\":\"section\",\"title\":\"Copy of Section 4\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"row\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"column\",\"_active\":true,\"size\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"line\",\"elements\":[],\"line_color\":\"hsl(0, 0%, 100%)\"},{\"_type\":\"custom-headline\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"Intro\"},{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"text_align\":\"l\",\"content\":\"Hey business owners today I\'m going to talk about 5 ways that you can increase the amount of people joining your email list.nnBefore we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is the fourth builder of you before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is important to be building your email list everyday nnWhy is email important for my business?nnHaving someone who might be interested in your services give you your email, is now more valuable than ever. I would rather have 1000 emails of potential prospects, than 5000 home addresses of the same prospects to send physical mail to.nnTactic #1nOffer a discount on your servicesnnIf you were in the low ticket industry, offering a discount on your products or even in some cases a free product, is a great way to get your customers to visit your website with an ad or opt in the email so that you can target them later. nnIf you\'re hoping that people will care to opt into your newsletter without you offering anything additional to that, you\'re going to be sadly mistaken these days.nnFrom AB test we\'ve run where we had email often forms offering nothing other than just updates and tips compared to opt in form is offering things such as a free download of some digital content, we saw often rates jumped by at least 5x.nnThis percentage increase varies depending on the industry, but overall giving something valuable to the consumer in exchange for them giving you their email, produces significantly more opt ins.nnTactic #2nHost an old-fashioned giveawaynnWhen you see those ads on Facebook giving away free things, (usually electronics), take a second to look at that next time. You\'re going to fine they want something in return, usually it\'s an email, share, or like.nnNow let\'s take it a step further rather than giving away just a free iPhone or something meaningless like that. Give away something that your ideal customers would want.nnYou might need to get a little creative.nnIf you\'re in the automotive industry, give away a new set of tires. If you\'re in the home remodeling space, give away a brand-new bathroom remodel. If you were in the restaurant industry (which is a little easier because who doesn\'t like to eat), offer a free dinner to one lucky winner.nnDepending on if you do your marketing right, this can generate hundreds if not thousands of people that would be interested in your product or service. You can quickly see how that would easily cover the cost of the prize to the winner.nnnTactic #3n include a downloadable PDF of whatever topic it is your blogging aboutnnThis one works very well too, especially if you\'re in the high ticket industry.nnLet\'s say you do plumbing and HVAC. nnA great example of this would be a 15 point checklist of things you can do as a homeowner to prevent damage to your plumbing and HVAC system.nnSome of you might be thinking right now, \"But why would I tell my potential customers how not to need me?\".nnEasy.nnGuess who\'s going to be top of mind when something does go wrong with their plumbing or HVAC?nnJoe Schmo\'s Plumbing on Yelp?nnOr you, the person who gave them a free resource without asking for anything but an email, and have been periodically providing free preventative care value to them via email?nnThe goal is to make yourself be the person I think about when they might need your services.nnnTactic #3nHost a giveawaynn Regardless of your industry, I\'m sure there is something that you can find valuable to your potential customers to give away for free. Giveaways are not a thing of the past, they have worked extremely well for some of our clients.nnLet\'s say you\'re in the home inspection industry. You could be giving away a free home inspection to one person who enters.nnThe requirementsnMake sure that the competition is social, social proof will help out immensely in getting even more people to join a giveaway. The most common form of entering a game wa make sure that the competition is social, social proof will help out immensely in getting even more people to join a giveaway. The most common form of entering a giveaway,  is by asking your potential customers to Upton with their email address.nnThe less hurdles you make your audience jump through, and the more\"}]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/3\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}],\"_column_layout\":\"1/1\"}],\"padding\":[\"20px\",\"10%\",\"45px\",\"10%\",\"unlinked\"]}]'),(960,3730,'_cornerstone_excerpt','Learn marketing tactics to increase the amount of potential customers signing up to join your email list. Hey business owners today I&#8217;m going to talk about 5 ways that you can increase the amount of people joining your email list. Before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is the fourth builder of you before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is important to be building your email list everyday  Why is email important for my business? Having someone who might be interested in your services give you your email, is now more valuable than ever. I would rather have 1000 emails of potential prospects, than 5000 home addresses of the same prospects to send physical mail to.'),(961,3730,'_cornerstone_version','1.3.3'),(962,3749,'inline_featured_image','0'),(963,3749,'_yst_is_cornerstone',''),(964,3749,'_edit_last','1'),(965,3749,'_cornerstone_settings','{\"custom_css\":\"/*nNo need for style tags here;nsimply get started by writingnCSS! Watch as your changesnare reflected live in thenpreview area. Have fun!n*/nn/* Typography */na {n  color:#43b2b5;n}nnp {n  color:#42464D;n  font-size: 18px;n  line-height: 50px;n}nnbr {n   display: block;n   margin: 30px 0;n}nnn.entry-title {ntext-align: center;n  font-size: 200%;n}n.entry-title:hover{n  color: #53BEC1;n}nn/* Body Padding Fix */nn.entry-wrap {n    display: block;n    padding: 60px 0px 0px 0px;n    box-shadow: none;n}nn.x-sidebar.right {n      padding: 60px 0px 0px 0px;n}nn/* Body Padding Fix */nn.popout {n  tmargin-top:40px;n    text-align: center;n    font-weight: 600;n    color: #fff;n    display: block;n    background: #2e3638;n    padding: 30px;n    border-radius: 10px;n}nn.quote {ntcolor: gray;n  font-size: 1.1em;n  font-style: italic;n  font-weight: 100;n}\",\"custom_js\":\"//n// No need to add script tagsn// here; simply get startedn// by writing JavaScript!n// Remember to save yourn// changes to see them :)n//nn\",\"custom_js_mini\":\"\",\"responsive_text\":[]}'),(966,3749,'_x_entry_body_css_class',''),(967,3749,'_x_entry_alternate_index_title',''),(968,3749,'_x_entry_bg_image_full',''),(969,3749,'_x_entry_bg_image_full_fade','750'),(970,3749,'_x_entry_bg_image_full_duration','7500'),(971,3749,'_x_post_layout',''),(972,3749,'_cornerstone_data','[{\"_type\":\"section\",\"title\":\"Intro\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"row\",\"_column_layout\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"column\",\"_active\":true,\"size\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"image\",\"elements\":[],\"src\":\"https://codelabstudios.dev/app/uploads/2017/04/emails.jpg\"},{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"In modern business, maintaining a strong relationship with your clients has become a key part of business growth.n</br>Even though many aspects of businesses are becoming automated, customer relations are one thing which canu2019t be automated without being easily noticeable.nnWithin minutes of a customer alerting you of their unhappiness towards your service, they can quickly publish their (albeit unwanted) opinion to social media and tarnish the reputation which youu2019ve carefully built up. nn<a href=\"\">Because of this, if you havenu2019t done so already, then you should prioritise the relationships which you have with your customers.n\"}]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}]}],\"padding\":[\"45px\",\"0px\",\"35px\",\"0px\",\"unlinked\"]},{\"_type\":\"section\",\"title\":\"Section 4\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"row\",\"_column_layout\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"column\",\"_active\":true,\"size\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"<span class=\"quote\">Do what you do so well that they will want to see it again and bring their friends.u201d u2013 <strong>Walt Disney</strong></span>\",\"text_align\":\"c\"},{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"<span class=\"popout\">Hey! This is the <a href=\"#\">.popout</a> class! Use it wisely.</span> \"}]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}]}],\"padding\":[\"0px\",\"0px\",\"45px\",\"0px\",\"unlinked\"]},{\"_type\":\"section\",\"title\":\"Section 2\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"row\",\"_column_layout\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"column\",\"_active\":true,\"size\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"With more and more businesses arising every day, every industryu2019s competition is growing and because of this, a high-standard of customer relations is expected. Businesses who donu2019t prioritise this are simply expected to fail; itu2019s true, if you donu2019t prioritise customer relations then you will fail as a business.n\"},{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"Here are some statistics from 2012 to back up this claim:\",\"text_align\":\"c\"},{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"<hr>n<ul>n<li>A measly 37% of businesses received the ratings u201cExcellentu201d and u201cGoodu201d for their customer relations. On the other hand, 63% of businesses received either u201cOkayu201d, u201cPooru201d, or u201cVery Pooru201d ratings for their customer relations.</li>n<hr>n<li>Following a poor experience, 89% took to a businesses competitors instead.</li>n<hr>n<li> 60% of customers would rather pay more money for good customer relations, opposed to having a cheap service with a poor customer experience.</li>n<hr>n<li>On average, businesses who lost a customer to one of their competitors lost $289 per lost customer.</li>n</ul>\"}]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}]}],\"padding\":[\"0px\",\"0px\",\"45px\",\"0px\",\"unlinked\"]},{\"_type\":\"section\",\"title\":\"Section 3\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"row\",\"_column_layout\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"column\",\"_active\":true,\"size\":\"1/1\",\"elements\":[{\"_type\":\"text\",\"elements\":[],\"content\":\"These statistics speak for themselves and go to show that if you donu2019t already do so, then itu2019s time to prioritise customer relations and make sure that your customers have the best experience possible.nWith that, below we have put together 6 of the best ways to make customers love your business as well as increase the number of customers that you receive.n#1 u2013 Interact With Your CustomersnAs we mentioned above, businesses are beginning to be automated and so they are missing out on the u201cpersonalu201d level of their service. Although automation can be helpful, thereu2019s one thing that it wonu2019t help you with. Interacting with your customers.nActually interacting with your customers rather than just providing them with a service is important as it goes to show that you genuinely care about providing a top-notch service and letu2019s face it, if you donu2019t interact with your customers then youu2019re going to lose potential clients and fail as a business.nOn top of that, donu2019t talk to them like a robot. Youu2019re not talking to the press or publishing a scientific study, so speak to them as if they were in front of you and you are having a conversation. Make them feel like you care about their needs and what theyu2019re looking for in a business, and youu2019ll undoubtedly have a long-time customer.n#2 u2013 Listen to Your CustomersnA lot of businesses nowadays have become egotistical and disregard customer feedback due to the fact that it isnu2019t a professional opinion. Although this is true, customer feedback can help you to improve your everyday business and find out what it was that your customers liked about the service which you provide, as well as the things they didnu2019t like.nThere are a few different ways to get feedback from customers youu2019ve dealt with, such as:nu2022tSocial media pagesnu2022tAsking potential customers through relevant communitiesnu2022tSimply asking customers who youu2019ve worked with in the pastnu2022tEmailing customers which a survey which is relevant to the service that you provided them withnThese are just a few of the most effective ways to gather helpful feedback to improve your service overall, and ultimately increase your customer count.n#3 u2013 Provide TransparencynCustomers want to know everything about your business and they donu2019t want to jump through hoops just to find out details about you that they should otherwise know. Because of that, transparency is something which is expected from businesses nowadays. This is especially important for online businesses.nWhat does it mean for a business to be transparent?nu2022tTransparency is when you donu2019t avoid your customers.nu2022tTransparency is when you welcome any feedback which you receive from your customers.nu2022tTransparency is when you and your employees donu2019t have to alter your personalities at work.nu2022tTransparency is when you donu2019t have anything to hide.nGiven that there are still businesses out there who donu2019t provide transparency, by incorporating it into your business and having nothing to hide, youu2019re giving yourself a leg up over your competitors. n#4 u2013 Keep Your WordnContinuing up on the previous point, keeping your word and not letting your customer down helps to build trust between you and your customers. If you make promises which you yourself are unsure about, or which you know you canu2019t keep, then your customers will lose trust in you and will know that you arenu2019t a reliable business to deal with.nu201cYour word is your bond.u201d u2013 Melvyn DouglasnIf you arenu2019t able to keep a promise that you are going to make, cut yourself off and donu2019t make that promise. If you arenu2019t able to meet your customeru2019s deadline, let them know before itu2019s too late.nBe comfortable with the work that you take on, donu2019t take on more work than you or your busine\nss is not capable of completing in the timespan which is provided, and complete it to your best standard. By doing this your customers will see you as a reliable business who they can trust and will return to you in the future.n#5 u2013 Relax and RespectnAround 1 in every 3 customers have said that they have experienced rude customer service a minimum of once a month. Following this, roughly 58-percent of these people will tell their friends about this rude experience.nWord of mouth has always been, and will also be, an effective way of marketing. However, there is such as a thing as bad word of mouth and this is a prime example of it. If you find that your employees are rude or that you could be more pleasant when dealing with customers, itu2019s in your best interests to deal with it effectively.nEvery business has customers who arenu2019t the easiest to work with although this is the sort of thing that you have to have patience for, relax, and deal with appropriately. If you relax and come to an outcome which suits both you and the problematic customer, youu2019ll both leave somewhat satisfied.nBy having respect for your customers and dealing with the issues that they have, theyu2019ll provide you with u201cgood word of mouthu201d. n#6 u2013 Be a Pleasure to Work WithnThe last thing that weu2019re going to discuss is your attitude. Always have a positive attitude when it comes to your business and donu2019t let your personal life get involved with your work. This can cause your business to take a hit if your anger is misdirected, and this is often not something which you can recover from easily.nIf you are in need of more details from a customer to get started on the service you are providing, always say u201cPleaseu201d. When they get back to you or compliment the work which youu2019ve done for them, always say u201cThank Youu201d. These may seem like basic manners although they can really go a long way.nAppreciate your customers and theyu2019ll appreciate you.n\"}]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]},{\"_type\":\"column\",\"size\":\"1/1\",\"_active\":false,\"elements\":[]}]}],\"padding\":[\"px\",\"0px\",\"45px\",\"0px\",\"unlinked\"]}]'),(973,3749,'_cornerstone_excerpt','Within minutes of a customer alerting you of their unhappiness towards your service, they can quickly publish their (albeit unwanted) opinion to social media and tarnish the reputation which youve carefully built up.  Because of this, if you havent done so already, then you should prioritise the relationships which you have with your customers. Do what you do so well that they will want to see it again and bring their friends.  Walt Disney Hey! This is the .popout class! Use it wisely.  With more and more businesses arising every day, every industrys competition is growing and because of this, a high-standard of customer relations is expected. Businesses who dont prioritise this are simply expected to fail; its true, if you dont prioritise customer relations then you will fail as a business.'),(974,3749,'_cornerstone_version','1.3.3'),(975,3987,'inline_featured_image','0'),(976,3987,'_yst_is_cornerstone',''),(977,3987,'_edit_last','1'),(978,3987,'_cornerstone_settings','{\"custom_css\":\"/*nNo need for style tags here;nsimply get started by writingnCSS! Watch as your changesnare reflected live in thenpreview area. Have fun!n*/nn/* Typography */na {n  color:#43b2b5;n}nnp {n  color:#42464D;n  font-size: 18px;n  line-height: 50px;}nn.entry