al customers),<strong>while theyre browsing Facebook</strong>.\n\nYou can even display ads to people who have purchased from you in the past. Display up-sells, cross-sells, etc and bring them back to your site every time.\n\nAnyone that visits your website can automatically be put into whats called a<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/business/help/341425252616329\"><strong>Facebook Custom Audience</strong></a>(and then into a Remarketing List).\n<blockquote><span class=\"box\"><span id=\"item\"><a href=\"https://emailoctopus.com/\">What is a Facebook Custom Audience?</a></span>\nA Custom Audience from a customer list is a type of audience you can create made up of your existing customers. You can target ads to the audience youve created on Facebook, Instagram, and Audience Network.</span>\n\n<i>Source: Facebook Help Center</i></blockquote>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2 id=\"Importance\">Why is this so important?</h2>\nNow heres the fun part.\n\n<strong>Anytime someone visits your website, they are anonymously saved to your custom audience.</strong>\n\n<strong>Then, the next time they are on Facebook, they are going to see YOUR ADS in their news feed or side bar.</strong>\n\nMost people are on Facebook at some point these days, including your target customer, roughly<strong>2 billion people/month</strong>log on.\n\nSo these people seeing your ads are going to be<strong>very likely to purchase or sign up</strong>because theyve already been to your website and are most likely interested in what you have to offer.\n<h2 id=\"GetStarted\">How to Get Started</h2>\nIn order to build a custom audience from people who have purchased from you or<strong>visited your website</strong>(which are some of the best kind of people by the way  it makes sense, theyve raised their hand and shown an interest in what you have to offer as a business), you need install a<strong>Facebook Pixel</strong>.\n\n<i>*This part you might need to be a little technically inclined for or send this guide to someone who is.</i>\n\n</div>\n<blockquote>How to Install your Facebook Pixel (Free Guide)\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/business/help/952192354843755\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.facebook.com/business/help/952192354843755</a></blockquote>\n<i>The page will look something like this:</i>\n\n</div>\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-5042 size-full\" src=\"http://codelabstudios.com/app/uploads/2018/02/Facebook-Pixel-Guide-min.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"447\" />\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n&nbsp;\n<h5 id=\"Audience\">How to Create the Audience</h5>\n<blockquote><span class=\"popout\">Visit your Facebook Ads Manager\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ads/manager/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.facebook.com/business/help/952192354843755</a></span></blockquote>\nOnce youre in your<strong>Facebook Ads Manager</strong>, go ahead and click on the<img src=\"https://codelabstudios.dev/app/uploads/2017/08/Hamburger.jpg\" />and follow the instructions in the images below.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-5041\" src=\"http://codelabstudios.com/app/uploads/2018/02/Steps-1-and-2-min.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"734\" height=\"268\" />\n\nAnd thats basically it for the basics on setting up a custom audience for remarketing.\n\n<hr />\n\n<h6 id=\"Conclusion\">Conclusion</h6>\nThis is just the beginners guide on<strong>what is Facebook Remarketing &amp; How to get Started</strong>. It gets complicated from here when it comes down to targeting the audience, creating ads, A/B testing campaigns, optimizing for conversions, getting people to actually buy from you, and scaling up. If youre not careful, you can waste money.\n<blockquote><span class=\"popout\">If Facebook Advertising sounds like something youd want to look into, give us a call and get some free advice.</span></blockquote>\n&nbsp;','What is Facebook Remarketing and is it Important?','','inherit','closed','closed','','4191-autosave-v1','','','2018-02-14 05:20:54','2018-02-14 10:20:5